click here
or call our toll free number at (877) 365-3500.
Virginia Residents:
If you would like further information regarding your legal rights under Virginia law or would like to exercise any of them, please
click here
.
Notice of Right to Opt Out of Sale of Personal Information or Sharing or Processing Information for Targeted Advertising.
California and Virginia residents may opt out of the “sale” of their personal information or processing or sharing of your information for online targeted advertising purposes.  We sell or share certain of your information to third parties to provide you with offers and promotions and opportunities that may be of interest to you.  We also allow third parties to receive certain information, such as cookies, IP address, and/or browsing behavior, to deliver targeted advertising to you on the Services or other services.  This activity may also be considered a sale under applicable law. Advertising, including targeted advertising, enables us to provide you certain content for free and allows us to provide you offers relevant to you.
Depending on what Services you use, we may provide the following categories of personal information to third parties for these purposes:
For online targeted advertising purposes: demographic and statistical information, user-generated content, contact information, device information and identifiers, connection and usage data, geolocation, and social media information.
For sharing with third parties to send you relevant offers and promotions and opportunities:  contact and registration information; demographic and statistical information, employment and education data, user-generated content, and geolocation.
If you would like to opt out of SM’s use of your information for such purposes, you may do so as outlined on the following page:
Your Privacy Choices
. You can also submit an opt-out request for contact and other non-cookie or similar tracker based information by emailing us at
privacysupport@sheknows.com
. Please note that we do not knowingly sell the personal information of minors under 16 years of age without legally-required affirmative authorization.
Even if you opt out, you will still see advertising from SM and its third party vendors, it just may be less relevant to you, or it may be personalized for you based only on the data that SM has collected about you.   You must opt out on each device and each browser where you want your choice to apply. Your preference may be lost if you clear, or your browser is set to clear, cookies.  If you have enabled a legally recognized browser-based opt out preference signal (such as Global Privacy Control) on your browser, we recognize such preference in accordance and to the extent required by applicable law. You will need to turn this on for each browser you use.
Non-Discrimination.
Applicable law may further provide you with the right to not be discriminated against (as provided for in applicable law) for exercising rights.
8. Your Choices about Ads and Analytics
To learn more about how to manage your preferences regarding our cookie-based advertising in addition to the options outlined above, please see the “Cookie Management” section in our Cookie Notice
below
.
Please note that you may still receive (from us or third parties) and SM and  third parties on our behalf may still serve advertisements within the Publisher Network Websites even if you opt out of tailored advertising, but the ads delivered by us will not be based on your activity across unrelated web sites or apps.
Do Not Track.
SM does not act on “do not track” requests from your browser because, this way, we are able to personalize your experiences on the Publisher Network Websites. For more information, go to
http://www.networkadvertising.org
or
http://www.aboutads.info
.  Please note that “Do Not Track” is a distinct privacy mechanism from the legally recognized browser-based opt out signals described above, which we honor in accordance with applicable law.
9. Retention of Your Information
We keep your information for no longer than necessary for the purposes for which it is processed. The length of time for which we retain information depends on the purposes for which we collected and use it and/or as required to comply with applicable laws.
10. Cookies and Other Tracking Technologies
We use and allow certain other companies to use certain tracking technologies, including cookies, web beacons, and other similar technologies (collectively, “
Cookies
”) on the Publisher Network Websites. This section (“
Cookie Notice
”) explains what these technologies are and why we use them, as well as your rights to control our use of them.
What are Cookies?
Cookies are text files that contain a certain amount of information and are downloaded to your computer or mobile device when you visit a website. They are useful because they allow websites to recognize a user's device. They are then returned to the original website on each subsequent visit or to any other website that recognizes them. For more information on cookies, go to
www.allaboutcookies.org
.
The term "
Cookie
" is used in this Notice in the broad sense to include all similar techniques and technology, including web beacons and log files. For more information on these additional tools, see our glossary below.
Types of Information We Collect
Cookies help us to understand Publisher Network Website usage and to improve the advertising content and offerings on the Publisher Network Websites. Examples of the types of information that we collect through Cookies include:
The number of users visiting Publisher Network Websites, the number of times a Publisher Network Website was viewed, the pages or ads viewed, the clicks made on the Publisher Network Websites or ads and the total duration of navigation on the Publisher Network Websites;
The name of the page that referred you to the Publisher Network Websites;
Whether this is your first time visiting the Publisher Network Websites;
Your viewing preferences (e.g. layout, sizing preferences, language etc.); and
Your the type of browser used and your IP address, so that we can identify you during your next visits.
How We Use Cookies
Examples of ways that we use Cookies include:
To control the display of ads;
To track usage patterns on the Publisher Network Websites; and
To personalize information.
SM (or third party service providers on our behalf) may also use cookies to collect aggregate information about Publisher Network Website users. We may share aggregate demographic and usage information with our prospective and actual business partners, advertisers and other third parties for any business purpose.
Types of Cookies We Use on Our Publisher Network Websites
We use Cookies for several reasons. Some Cookies also enable us to track and target the interests of our users and to enhance the experience on our Publisher Network Websites. Third parties, including those acting on your behalf and those that may be not acting on our behalf, also serve Cookies through the Publisher Network Websites for advertising, analytics and other purposes. The specific types of Cookies served by SM through our Publisher Network Websites and the functions they perform are described in more detail below.  As a reminder, we do not operate or own the Publisher Network Websites and such Websites will include other cookies.  You should review the Publisher Network Websites’ privacy policies for more information.
Functional Cookies
: These cookies allow certain aspects of the ads to function.  To refuse these Cookies, please follow the instructions below under the section Cookie Management. Note that by disabling functional cookies, certain ad features may not function properly.
Embedded Scripts.
An embedded script is programming code that is designed to collect information about your interactions with the Publisher Network Websites, such as the links you click on. The code is temporarily downloaded onto your computer or other device, is active only while you are connected to the Publisher Network Websites, and is deactivated or deleted thereafter.
Cross-Device and Analytic Cookies
: SM may use cookies in combination with the information we collect from third parties or from our affiliates such as PMC— for instance, IP addresses and unique mobile device identifiers — to locate or try to locate the same unique users across multiple browsers or devices (such as smartphones or tablets), or work with service providers that do this, in order to save your preferences across devices and analyze usage of the Publisher Network Websites. To refuse these Cookies, you may install the Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on by clicking
here
.
We and our third party partners (including advertisers) may set and access Cookies on your computer as well. We do not have control over how third parties use such cookies and similar technologies or the information derived therefrom, and this Ad Services Privacy Policy does not cover any use of information that such third parties may have collected from you or the methods used by the third-parties to collect that information. These types of cookies include:
Advertising Cookies
: These Cookies  collect several types of data about your browsing habits, as well as your preferences for products and services. This information allows SM to serve you relevant advertisements on the Publisher Network Websites. To refuse these cookies from us or our vendors, please follow the instructions below under the section Cookie Management. Some advertisements may also contain an icon that you may click on to find out more about how to manage your advertising preferences.
